The Definition of Photon Energy

The energy of a photon is equal to Planck's constant multiplied by the frequency of the photon.

E = hf

where:

E [var. Energy] is the energy of the photon
h [const. PlancksConstant] is Planck's constant
f [var. Frequency] is the frequency of the photon

